The Nairobi Metropolitan Services (NMS) and Woodley tenants are headed for a clash over the redevelopment of the old city estate.
This comes after the residents moved to court seeking to stop the planned redevelopment of the estate until all issues surrounding its ownership are dealt with.
Consequently, the tenants have said they will not attend a planned public participation on the project planned for today (Monday).



