On Wednesday last week, NMS called for views from tenants of county rental houses to be affected by the planned redevelopment of 10 old Nairobi County estates with public participation set to begin on February 8, 2021 at Joseph Kang’ethe Social Hall in Woodley.
However, the tenants, through the Woodley Residents Welfare Society (WRWS), have said they will not attend the meeting, claiming the NMS did not follow procedure on public participation.



